C Berkeley campus</a>. Occurring on the same night as the university-nationalist \"USC Bonfire\" rivalry party, Occuparty decided to parody these tropes of competition by presenting itself as the real enemy of the standing university. Ritualistically covered up for the week preceding the cross-town rivalry football game against USC, the Bruin Bear\'s encasement became subject to student and community messages deriding the governments lack of attention to the university population. The banner questioning \"Public or Private?\" spanned the protective box, along with other statements like \"End Apathy\", \"Cut military spending-rebuild America\", and \"Prop 13\" written inside of a crossed out circle.</p>'),(8628,51,2,38,0,'<kml xmlns=\"http://earth.google.com/kml/2.0\"><Folder><name>OpenLayers export</name><description>Exported on Fri Nov 02 2012 17:30:35 GMT-0700 (Pacific Daylight Time)</description><Placemark><name>OpenLayers.Feature.Vector_169</name><description>No description available</description><Polygon><outerBoundaryIs><LinearRing><coordinates>-13185229.725988,4038363.0133012 -13185173.592545,4038340.3210584 -13185208.228073,4038277.0216444 -13185244.05793,4038281.7989586 -13185250.029573,4038334.3494156 -13185236.891959,4038342.7097155 -13185229.725988,4038363.0133012</coordinates></LinearRing></outerBoundaryIs></Polygon></Placemark></Folder></kml>|16|-13185191.507474|4038361.1022589|osm\r\n'),(8626,51,2,40,0,'November 21, 2011'),(8627,51,2,51,0,'Event'),(8635,50,2,48,1,'<p>\"<a title=\"14 Occupy UCLA protesters arrested, Wilson Plaza cleared in early morning shutdown\" href=\"http://www.dailybruin.com/blog/timestamp/2011/11/fourteen_occupy_ucla_protesters_arrested_wilson_plaza_cleared_in_early_morning_shutdown\" target=\"_blank\">14 Occupy&nbsp;<span class=\"caps\">UCLA</span>&nbsp;protesters arrested, Wilson Plaza cleared in early morning shutdown</a>\"</p>'),(8249,189,2,50,0,'Orpheum Theater'),(8250,189,2,49,0,'SIgns and signboards [LCSH]'),(8251,189,2,41,0,'\"The Orpheum Theatre on Broadway in downtown Los Angeles, California, opened on February 15, 1926, as the fourth and final Los Angeles venue for the Orpheum vaudeville circuit.\"'),(8606,72,2,40,0,'2012'),(8605,72,2,48,0,'\"A People\'s Guide To Los Angeles\"'),(8601,72,2,50,0,'The \"White Wall\", South Central Incinerator, and South Central Farm'),(8602,72,2,49,0,'Discrimination in housing [LCSH]'),(8603,72,2,41,0,'\"Before World War II, South L.A.\'s working-class neighborhoods were racially segregated by an invisible barrier known as the \"White Wall\" along Alameda Boulevard. African Americans lived to the west of Alameda, whites to the east.\r\n\r\nDuring the Watts uprising in 1965, Alameda emerged as racial dividing line...Many whites fled South Los Angeles immediately after the Watts uprising, citing Black violence and fears of school integration, and taking advantage of racially exclusive housing in the suburbs.\"\r\n(Pulido, et.al.)'),(8485,310,3,76,0,'FileName:d639d8d5de6fb76c6444eb969058ba07.jpg\nFileDateTime:1354868328\nFileSize:126257\nFileType:2\nMimeType:image/jpeg\nSectionsFound:ANY_TAG, IFD0, THUMBNAIL, EXIF\nCOMPUTED:\n	html:width=\"599\" height=\"393\"\n	Height:393\n	Width:599\n	IsColor:1\n	ByteOrderMotorola:1\n	Thumbnail.FileType:2\n	Thumbnail.MimeType:image/jpeg\n\nOrientation:1\nXResolution:720090/10000\nYResolution:720090/10000\nResolutionUnit:2\nSoftware:Adobe Photoshop CS4 Macintosh\nDateTime:2012:05:24 10:20:39\nExif_IFD_Pointer:164\nTHUMBNAIL:\n	Compression:6\n	XResolution:72/1\n	YResolution:72/1\n	ResolutionUnit:2\n	JPEGInterchangeFormat:302\n	JPEGInterchangeFormatLength:3481\n\nColorSpace:65535\nExifImageWidth:599\nExifImageLength:393\n'),(8629,50,2,50,0,'Wilson Plaza Occupation'),(8630,50,2,49,0,'Protest movements --United States--History--21st century [LCSH]\r\n'),(8631,50,2,49,0,'Occupy Wall Street (Movement) [LCSH]'),(8632,50,2,41,0,'In response to the recent eruption of Occupy Wall Street on September 17th, 2011, several hundred students and activists converged on Wilson Plaza on November 17th in order to address critical issues concerning higher education, namely burgeoning student debt, skyrocketing tuition costs, and lack of student governance over university function to name a few. Students and workers alike, alumnus, faculty articulated their concerns over the direction and affordability of and access to the university.\r\n\r\nGoing into the night, approximately 40 students and community members decided to Occupy--against school ordinances--Wilson Plaza. Early the next morning, protesters met no less than 100 police actors at the site of occupation, and were demanded to evacuate or else risk arrest. 14 activists ended up being arrested for charges of unlawful assembly and failure to disperse, which sparked the already burning debate within the community over what constitutes a space for free assembly and speech, and, more generally, to what extent do we control--not just \'own\'--our university.\r\n'),(8633,50,2,41,0,'“The messaging for the Thursday rally in Meyerhoff Park was related to the Occupy movement because of the large impact this movement has had across the globe. The University of California Students Association priorities of progressive taxation and corporate tax reform fit well into the larger context of this movement.”\r\nDaily Bruin November 22, 2011\r\n\r\n\"Police arrested 14 people participating in the Occupy UCLA campout in Wilson Plaza while clearing the plaza early this morning. The protesters were arrested on charges of unlawful assembly and failure to disperse, a university spokesman said. \"\r\nDaily Bruin November 18, 2011'),(8536,192,2,40,0,'2001'),(8534,192,2,39,0,'Harry Benson (photographer)'),(8535,192,2,48,0,'http://lissgallery.com/?page_id=317'),(8531,192,2,50,0,'White police officer surveys slain Black man'),(8766,170,2,50,0,'Point lettering Superimposed Over Old English lettering'),(6920,295,3,76,0,'FileName:c066e38f1bcb730377d1cb524cc5793f.jpg\nFileDa