ched an investigation of the Sinarquistas, an anti-Communist society that had tried to influence politics in Mexico and was charged with perpetrating subversive activities in the barrios of Los Angeles. The hearings of this committee, which continued from 1940 until 1945, contributed to the city’s xenophobic response to the Mexican-American community during the entire decade.\" – eNotes.com Zoot Suit Riots'),(8340,253,2,48,0,'http://www.lataco.com/taco/zoot-suit-riots-1943'),(8028,243,2,7,0,'Photo'),(7146,298,3,74,0,'8'),(7147,298,3,75,0,'3'),(7148,298,3,77,0,'a:13:{s:8:\"FileName\";s:36:\"d9e28d8a2452574286c5c272e9b97b08.jpg\";s:12:\"FileDateTime\";i:1354240207;s:8:\"FileSize\";i:130293;s:8:\"FileType\";i:2;s:8:\"MimeType\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";s:13:\"SectionsFound\";s:19:\"ANY_TAG, IFD0, EXIF\";s:8:\"COMPUTED\";a:5:{s:4:\"html\";s:24:\"width=\"414\" height=\"729\"\";s:6:\"Height\";i:729;s:5:\"Width\";i:414;s:7:\"IsColor\";i:1;s:17:\"ByteOrderMotorola\";i:1;}s:11:\"XResolution\";s:4:\"72/1\";s:11:\"YResolution\";s:4:\"72/1\";s:14:\"ResolutionUnit\";i:2;s:16:\"Exif_IFD_Pointer\";i:78;s:14:\"ExifImageWidth\";i:414;s:15:\"ExifImageLength\";i:729;}'),(7149,298,3,76,0,'FileName:d9e28d8a2452574286c5c272e9b97b08.jpg\nFileDateTime:1354240207\nFileSize:130293\nFileType:2\nMimeType:image/jpeg\nSectionsFound:ANY_TAG, IFD0, EXIF\nCOMPUTED:\n	html:width=\"414\" height=\"729\"\n	Height:729\n	Width:414\n	IsColor:1\n	ByteOrderMotorola:1\n\nXResolution:72/1\nYResolution:72/1\nResolutionUnit:2\nExif_IFD_Pointer:78\nExifImageWidth:414\nExifImageLength:729\n'),(8352,251,2,50,0,'Zoot Suit Outfits'),(8541,180,2,48,0,'http://www.southcentralhistory.com/watts-riots.php'),(8540,180,2,48,0,'Los Angeles Times photographic archive, UCLA Library'),(7295,299,3,75,0,'3'),(7296,299,3,77,0,'a:8:{s:8:\"FileName\";s:37:\"5e5eba258ace610176b24c1c52636ab2.jpeg\";s:12:\"FileDateTime\";i:1354242155;s:8:\"FileSize\";i:33014;s:8:\"FileType\";i:2;s:8:\"MimeType\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";s:13:\"SectionsFound\";s