icly that Chicanos were being used as cannon fodder.\"(http://latinopia.com/latino-history/1970-national-chicano-moratorium/)'),(8529,255,2,39,0,'Poster: Malaquias Montoya\r\n'),(8530,255,2,48,0,'http://www.latinopov.com/blog/?p=6011'),(7392,303,3,76,0,'FileName:b6d00d36854a2f09d649c1df4e78e3b5.jpg\nFileDateTime:1354245883\nFileSize:237601\nFileType:2\nMimeType:image/jpeg\nSectionsFound:ANY_TAG, IFD0, EXIF\nCOMPUTED:\n	html:width=\"756\" height=\"612\"\n	Height:612\n	Width:756\n	IsColor:1\n	ByteOrderMotorola:1\n\nXResolution:72/1\nYResolution:72/1\nResolutionUnit:2\nExif_IFD_Pointer:78\nExifImageWidth:756\nExifImageLength:612\n'),(7393,303,3,73,0,'612'),(7394,303,3,72,0,'756'),(8521,257,2,48,1,'<a title=\"Chicano Moratorium Documentary\" href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=famNeiosTVk\" target=\"_blank\">Chicano Moratorium Documentary</a>'),(8520,257,2,39,0,'LMU Film Student Tom Myrdahl'),(8517,257,2,50,0,'Chicano Moratorium Documentary'),(8518,257,2,49,0,'Chicano Movement [LCSH]'),(8519,257,2,41,0,'\"On August 29, 1970, a \"Chicano Moratorium\" against the war in Vietnam was held in East L.A. Loyola-Marymount film student Tom Myrdahl shot this documentary, capturing the events that unfolded as law enforcement and protesters clashed in and around Laguna Park. This film has not been seen in nearly 40 years. Tom, who is still a working cameraman in Los Angeles, is putting this historic film on the web as a tribute to the brave citizens of East L.A. who came together 40 years ago to voice their dissent against the Vietnam War.\r\n\" (Youtube)'),(7370,302,3,74,0,'8'),(7371,302,3,75,0,'3'),(7372,302,3,77,0,'a:13:{s:8:\"FileName\";s:36:\"7a0ebc3d4ad1bc8bd596782aab10d263.jpg\";s:12:\"FileDateTime\";i:1354245538;s:8:\"FileSize\";i:58365;s:8:\"FileType\";i:2;s:8:\"MimeType\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";s:13:\"SectionsFound\";s:19:\"ANY_TAG, IFD0, EXIF\";s:8:\"COMPUTED\";a:5:{s:4:\"html\";s:24:\"width=\"910\" height=\"560\"\";s:6:\"Height\";i:560;s:5:\"Width\";i:910;s:7:\"IsColor\"