e to a confrontation that ensued when a white police officer pulled over a Black motorist. The confrontation escalated, the driver\'s mother fot involved, and observers openly challenged the police. The rest is history. The most important thing to understand is that this incident was simply the straw that broke the camel\'s back in terms of community/police tensions. Chief William Parker, who saw the civil rights movement as a communist plot and led the Los Angeles Police Department from 1950-1966, was determined to stomp out any attempts at social change.\r\n\r\nThe Watts riot itself was the largest instance of urban unrest in U.S. history up to that time, and it led to the almost complete out-migration of whites and abandonment of the area by corporate retail outlets, who fear damage to their properties and property values.\"\r\n(Pulido, et.al. 2012: 121)'),(8532,192,2,49,0,'Watts Riot, Los Angeles, Calif., 1965 [LCSH]'),(7720,218,2,40,0,'1910'),(6025,259,3,73,0,'363'),(6026,259,3,72,0,'1000'),(7721,218,2,44,0,'English'),(7722,218,2,38,0,'<kml xmlns=\"http://earth.google.com/kml/2.0\"><Folder><name>OpenLayers export</name><description>Exported on Thu Nov 22 2012 17:15:33 GMT-0800 (PST)</description></Folder></kml>||||osm\r\nEast Los Angeles'),(6024,259,3,76,0,'FileName:2cd5138632daf66e4023a58144e4570a.jpg\nFileDateTime:1353633848\nFileSize:92791\nFileType:2\nMimeType:image/jpeg\nSectionsFound:COMMENT\nCOMPUTED:\n	html:width=\"1000\" height=\"363\"\n	Height:363\n	Width:1000\n	IsColor:1\n\nCOMMENT:\n	0:CREATOR: gd-jpeg v1.0 (using IJG JPEG v62), quality = 90\n\n\n'),(6021,259,3,74,0,'8'),(6022,259,3,75,0,'3'),(6023,259,3,77,0,'a:8:{s:8:\"FileName\";s:36:\"2cd5138632daf66e4023a58144e4570a.jpg\";s:12:\"FileDateTime\";i:1353633848;s:8:\"FileSize\";i:92791;s:8:\"FileType\";i:2;s:8:\"MimeType\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";s:13:\"SectionsFound\";s:7:\"COMMENT\";s:8:\"COMPUTED\";a:4:{s:4:\"html\";s:25:\"width=\"1000\" height=\"363\"\";s:6:\"Height\";i:363;s:5:\"Width\";i:1000;s:7: