g, but people in all three vehicles exchanged fire. Orebo was thrown out of the car as it headed down the Florence Avenue off ramp. He had been shot in the head, back and left forearm. The shooting was ruled justifiable.\"</span>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<kml xmlns=\"http://earth.google.com/kml/2.0\"><Folder><name>OpenLayers export</name><description>Exported on Thu Nov 29 2012 11:44:38 GMT-0800 (PST)</description><Placemark><name>OpenLayers.Feature.Vector_6041</name><description>No description available</description><Point><coordinates>-13166975.608171,4025403.2200217</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder></kml>',0,100,'#ff1919',NULL,'#ffffff',50,10,10,10,1,4,NULL,1,0,1,61,NULL,NULL),(85,NULL,NULL,3,NULL,1,'Betty Jackson',NULL,'\"<span style=\"background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252); font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; line-height: 24px; font-size: 10pt;\">Jackson, a 59-year-old African-American, was riding in a small Datsun, moving eastbound on 51st Street, when her car slammed into the back of a</span><span style=\"background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252); font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; line-height: 24px; font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span><a title=\"Ford Motor Company\" href=\"http://www.laweekly.com/related/to/Ford+Motor+Company/\" data-omni-track=\"Inform-&gt;Click|keyword[Ford+Motor+Company]\" style=\"font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; line-height: 24px; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration: initial; color: rgb(37, 60, 135);\">Ford</a><span style=\"background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252); font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; line-height: 24px; font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252); font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; line-height: 24px; font-size: 10pt;\">van. Her death was ruled accidental.\"</span><div><span style=\"background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252); font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; line-height: 24px; font-size: 10pt;\"><br></span></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<kml xmlns=\"http://earth.google.com/kml/2.0\"><Folder><name>OpenLayers export</name><description>Exported on Thu Nov 29 2012 11:44:38 GMT-0800 (PST)</description><Placemark><name>OpenLayers.Feature.Vector_9111</name><description>No description available</description><Point><coordinates>-13166201.683259,4028331.7136673</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder></kml>',0,100,'#ff1925',NULL,'#ffffff',50,10,10,10,1,4,NULL,1,0,1,62,NULL,NULL),(86,NULL,NULL,3,NULL,1,'Alfred Miller',NULL,'\"<span style=\"background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252); font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; line-height: 24px; font-size: 10pt;\">Alfred Miller, a 32-year-old African-American, was shot in the neck in a drive-by shooting. The bullet broke two of his vertebrae, hit his spine and lodged in his shoulder. It appears an arrest was made, but the D.A. declined to prosecute.\"</span><div><span style=\"background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252); font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; line-height: 24px; font-size: 10pt;\"><br></span></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<kml xmlns=\"http://earth.google.com/kml/2.0\"><Folder><name>OpenLayers export</name><description>Exported on Thu Nov 29 2012 11:44:38 GMT-0800 (PST)</description><Placemark><name>OpenLayers.Feature.Vector_12260</name><description>No description available</description><Point><coordinates>-13171098.430382,4027887.4234405</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder></kml>',0,100,'#ff1925',NULL,'#ffffff',50,10,10,10,1,4,NULL,1,0,1,63,NULL,NULL),(87,NULL,NULL,3,NULL,1,'Kevin Andrew Evanshren',NULL,'\"<span style=\"background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252); font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; line-height: 24px; font-size: 10pt;\">Homicide investigators nicknamed Evanshen the Good Samaritan. His mistake was trying to put out a fire started by looters at a check-cashing store. The 24-year-old white man slipped through a weakened portion of the office roof and died from burns and smoke inhalation.\"</span><div><span style=\"background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252); font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; line-height: 24px; font-size: 10pt;\"><br></span></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<kml xmlns=\"http://earth.google.com/kml/2.0\"><Folder><name>OpenLayers export</name><description>Exported on Thu Nov 29 2012 11:44:38 GMT-0800 (PST)</description><Placemark><name>OpenLayers.Feature.Vector_16140</name><description>No description available</description><Point><coordinates>-13182081.475882,4027633.0314558</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder></kml>',0,100,'#ff191d',NULL,'#fcfcfc',50,10,10,10,1,4,NULL,1,0,1,64,NULL,NULL),(88,NULL,NULL,3,NULL,1,'Wilson Alvarez&nbsp;',NULL,'\"<span style=\"background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252); font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; line-height: 24px; font-size: 10pt;\">Authorities believe looters fatally beat Alvarez with sticks after the 40-year-old transient started throwing rocks at them to break up a stealing spree. Alvarez died on May 23.</span><span style=\"background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252); font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; line-height: 24px; font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://www.laweekly.com/related/to/Gardena/\" data-omni-track=\"Inform-&gt;Click|keyword[Gardena]\" style=\"font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; line-height: 24px; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration: initial; color: rgb(37, 60, 135);\">Gardena</a><span style=\"background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252); font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; line-height: 24px; font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252); font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; line-height: 24px; font-size: 10pt;\">homicide 